title: Ramjas protests LIVE: AISA begins march against ABVP; Gurmehar Kaur withdraws from 'Fightback DU' campaign​ | Zee News
text:
Comment Pic 
New Delhi: After the Delhi University Students’ Union (DUSU) held a 'Tiranga March' from Ramjas College to Arts Faculty on Monday, students from various DU colleges will be marching on Tuesday protesting against the vandalism that happened in Ramjas College on February 22. 
The march, which will start at 12:30 pm, will begin from SGTB Khalsa College. 
Here are the live updates: Latest Updates 13:09 PM 
Wrestler Babita Phogat, after Virendra Sehwag and Yogeshwar Dutt, lashes out at LSR student Gurmehar Kaur, sides with ABVP 
"Jo aapne desh ke haq m bat nhi kar sakti uske haq m bat karna thik h kya??? I condemn rape threats If log iss tarah se dhamki de rahe h to ye bahut hi galat bat h.Lekin m aapne desh k khilaf single word nhi sun sakti," she said in a series of tweets Jo aapne desh ke haq m bat nhi kar sakti uske haq m bat karna thik h kya??? https://t.co/t4Xb0AELHi
